---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Weather Words — Highest Scoring Storm Vocabulary"
  description="Top weather words valid in Scrabble ranked by score. BLIZZARD (28pts), CYCLONE (14pts), TYPHOON (15pts), SQUALL (15pts), FREEZE (18pts), GUST (5pts). Free word finder."
  keywords="scrabble weather words, blizzard scrabble points, cyclone scrabble, typhoon scrabble word, squall scrabble, freeze scrabble, weather vocabulary scrabble, high scoring weather words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Weather Words — Highest Scoring Storm Vocabulary",
    "description": "Top weather words valid in Scrabble ranked by score. BLIZZARD (28pts), CYCLONE (14pts), TYPHOON (15pts), SQUALL (15pts), FREEZE (18pts), GUST (5pts).",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-weather-words" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the highest scoring weather word in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "BLIZZARD scores 28 points (B=3, L=1, I=1, Z=10, Z=10, A=1, R=1, D=2). It uses both Z tiles and qualifies as a bingo (8 letters through an existing tile), earning 78+ points total." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is TYPHOON a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, TYPHOON is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS, scoring 15 points (T=1, Y=4, P=3, H=4, O=1, O=1, N=1). It refers to a violent tropical cyclone in the western Pacific." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What short weather words score well in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "GUST scores 5 points in 4 letters. FOG (7pts), HAZE (16pts with Z=10), and ICY (8pts) are other short weather words that fit tight board positions effectively." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Weather Words — Highest Scoring Storm Vocabulary</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">��</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Weather vocabulary brings natural scoring power to your Scrabble rack. From the double-Z monster BLIZZARD to the quick-play GUST, meteorological terms cover every score tier and tile combination.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">28 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BLIZZARD (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Premium Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">95 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Combined Top 6</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letters (Bingo!)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 6 Weather Words by Score</h2>
      <p>These six weather words deliver the highest base scores. BLIZZARD stands out as a bingo play — use all 7+ tiles and earn the 50-point bonus on top.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">BLIZZARD — 28 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">B=3, L=1, I=1, Z=10, Z=10, A=1, R=1, D=2 · 8 letters · Bingo eligible</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Uses both Z tiles for devastating effect. Play through an existing letter for the 50-point bingo bonus — 78 points before premium squares.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌨️ BLIZZARD</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">28 pts · 8 letters · Heavy snowstorm with double-Z</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">❄️ FREEZE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 pts · 6 letters · Ice over with Z=10 anchor</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌀 TYPHOON</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · 7 letters · Tropical cyclone Y=4, H=4</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💨 SQUALL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · 6 letters · Sudden wind with Q=10</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌪️ CYCLONE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · 7 letters · Rotating storm C=3, Y=4</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💨 GUST</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 pts · 4 letters · Quick burst for tight spots</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Weather Words Worth Knowing</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HAZE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">THAW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SLEET</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FROST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOG</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DRIZZLE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Weather Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold Z for BLIZZARD:</span> If you draw one Z early, hold it. The second Z turns BLIZZARD into a bingo candidate worth 78+ points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SQUALL uses Q+U naturally:</span> When holding Q+U, SQUALL provides a reliable 15-point exit. SQUALLS hooks for 16 points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FREEZE for Z dump:</span> At 18 points for 6 tiles, FREEZE efficiently plays Z without needing both. Common surrounding tiles make it drawable.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">GUST for tight boards:</span> Only 4 tiles, 5 points — but fits where longer words can't. Access premium squares in cramped positions.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🧠 Weather Word Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Weather words use <span class="text-white font-medium">high-value consonants</span> (Z, Q, Y, H) paired with common vowels — excellent rack-balancers that play expensive tiles while keeping friendly letters for your next turn.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-science-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Science Words — Lab Vocabulary for High Scores</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/6-letter-words-with-z/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">6-Letter Words With Z — Complete Scrabble List</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid weather word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
